metadata.name: Neon Shadow #83
metadata.description:
A collection of geometric abstractions with architectural imagination.

The friction between painted and unpainted surfaces is what gives spatial depth to this work and makes you wonder whether you are looking from outside or inside.

Generative artwork by KINTSUGI BOI (@kintsugi_boi)

metadata.name: Tintinnabulum #5
metadata.description:
An audiovisual collection.
.
Click to start the sound.
..
Tintinnabulum is an endless generative music player.
...
There are 8 color palettes which correlate with 8 different root notes (C, G, F, D, Bb, A, Eb, B).

5 Noise types correlate with 5 different scales (Minor, Hicaz, Major, Lydian, Locrian) which have 2 registers.

2 different rhythmical structures (Polyrhthmic & standart). Each has 4 divisions.

2 rotation options; On, Off.
....
Harmonization process based on Avro Part's 'Tintinnabuli' style.

Made with p5.js and Web Audio.

Ilgın İçözü, November 2021
@distcollective

metadata.description: The creatures observed within the desolate cemetery of the city are commonly known as "pumpkin heads." metadata.name: indifferent age #18
metadata.description: The period of adolescence is like swinging on a rope stretched over a bottomless abyss. There are so many events, feelings, colors and momentous decisions on both sides. You are no longer a child, but you are not yet an adult. You are required to answer questions about your future that you don't have. You want to act on your own, but you're afraid of disappointing those who weren't prepared for the fact that you've grown up. You are drawn to make mistakes, but you are so reluctant to make them. Balancing over the precipice you have to watch out for so many factors that at some point you give up. Every detail of your vibrant life becomes indifferent to you. Of course, you'll realize that this was just a defensive reaction to internal and external stimuli. But how hard will be your memories of the time you spent swinging on a rope stretched over a bottomless abyss

metadata.name: Noodles #56
metadata.description:
The technical prophylaxis the brain performs from time to time is like a cruel joke. Because it does not warn us about what it is going to do and how we are going to feel about it.
There are times when we can't get our heads together. You know, there's a little confusion in the mind. I used to think of it as a mess of threads, tangled together and tied in knots that can't be untangled. It was a very naïve notion. I think the tangle of the mind is more like a noodle. Sticky, heavy, drawn-out and tasteless. Cold or hot, I don't know, but I don't like either. And the thoughts and images trapped in this mass certainly lend some flavor, though I'm not sure if that's good or bad. In the end, they just keep coming up over and over in your head, alternating and bringing nothing new to the table. It looks as if they are signaling you something and don't want to leave you alone, but they are just stuck in a noodle, just like you are.

metadata.name: Endless Ridge #98
metadata.description:
Generative scene programmed by GLSL, continuously changing its form with time.
Plenty of them maintain minimal with monotone,
some of them varied as light shined on them from time to time,
some of them are veiled with mist and clouds,
and few of them reflected silver light with special textures.

Minted one piece then you’ll own one view to observe.

Created by Natalie.J

metadata.name: Mosaic #835
metadata.description:
---
Notes:
- Click to pause/unpause
- The aspect ratio is fixed 1:1 because of the way the grid and movements are generated to make sure they're the same on all screens. 
---
Description:
An 80X80 grid of tiles are scrambled, shuffled, shifted, streamed, transported,
conveyed, moved, deposited. 

There are 15 initial tile states and 5 color palettes. A set of 12 unique motion patterns
are generated for each piece. 
---
Acknowledgements:
This piece is inspired by Kim Asendorf, whose pixel-level algorithms I'm
transfixed by, and Ksawery Komputery, whose algorithmic tile-works I'm crazy
about. 
---
Made by Sam Tsao (@sam___tsao) with P5.js 
December 2021, Germany
